  "text": "The Little Effect here considers the Kasha Effect [CITATION_1] within high spin, dense and strongly interacting spin systems. Such a high spin, dense system would allow the phonon bath to classically (via virtual states) excite electrons (the reverse Kasha Effect) between (stationary) orbital states rather than the opposite efficient relaxation of excited orbital states by creating phonons within the bosonic paired electrons.",
